type.name: blockLength
type.description: The total space reserved for the length of the message. Note that MEMO message do not use repeating groups or variable-length fields.

type.name: templateId
type.description: Identifier of the message template (ie. the message type).

type.name: schemaId
type.description: The identifier of a message schema. SchemaID=1 for MEMO version 1.

type.name: version
type.description: The version number of the message schema that was used to encode a message.

sbe:message.name: NewOrderSingle
sbe:message.description: The new order message type is used by institutions wishing to electronically submit securities orders to the exchange for execution.

field.name: ClOrdID
field.description: Unique identifier of the order as assigned by institution or by the intermediary (CIV term, not a hub/service bureau) with closest association with the investor.

field.name: OrderQty
field.description: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares.

field.name: Price
field.description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share).

field.name: ExecInst
field.description: Instructions for order handling on exchange.

field.name: PegOffsetValue
field.description: Amount (signed) added to the peg for a pegged order in the context of the PegOffsetType.

field.name: ExpireTime
field.description: Time/Date of order expiration, this is the expiration time of a Good Till Date TimeInForce.

field.name: MinQty
field.description: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed.

field.name: DisplayQty
field.description: Quantity of the order to be displayed.

field.name: DisplayMethod
field.description: Defines what value to use in DisplayQty (1138).

field.name: DisplayMinIncr
field.description: Defines the minimum increment to be used when calculating a random refresh of DisplayQty.

field.name: LocateReqd
field.description: Required on Short Sell orders only. Only acceptable value is 'N' which indicates the member have secured the required locate.

field.name: CancelGroupId
field.semanticType: Unique group identifier for mass cancel grouping

field.name: StpGroupId
field.semanticType: Unique group identifier for Self Trade Prevention grouping

field.name: SelfTradePrevention
field.description: Defines the desired behavior in the event of a wash.

field.name: RiskGroupId
field.semanticType: Unique group identifier for Risk grouping

sbe:message.name: OrderCancelReplaceRequest
sbe:message.description: The order cancel/replace request is used to change the parameters of an existing order.

field.name: OrigClOrdID
field.description: ClOrdID (11) of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the exchange, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

field.name: Symbol
field.description: This field may not change from the value stated in the original order.

field.name: SymbolSfx
field.description: This field may not change from the value stated in the original order.

field.name: Side
field.description: Side may only change between Sell, SellShort, and SellShortExempt.

field.name: OrderQty
field.description: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares. Increasing the size will cause the order to lose it's priority in the book.

field.name: OrdType
field.description: OrderType may only change from Limit order to Market order.

field.name: Price
field.description: Instructions for display the order. Changing the price will cause the order to lose it's priority in the book.

field.name: DisplayQty
field.description: Quantity of the order to be displayed.

field.name: LocateReqd
field.description: Required on Short Sell orders only. Only acceptable value is 'N' which indicates the member have secured the required locate.

sbe:message.name: OrderCancelRequest
sbe:message.description: The order cancel request message requests the cancellation all remaining size on an order.

field.name: OrigClOrdID
field.description: ClOrdID (11) of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the customer, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

field.name: OrderID
field.description: If specified only this OrderID will be canceled.

field.name: ClOrdID
field.description: A Unique identifier for the cancel request.

sbe:message.name: MassCancelRequest
sbe:message.description: The mass cancel request message requests the cancellation all remaining size on a set of existing orders that match the given criteria.

field.name: ClOrdID
field.description: A Unique identifier for the cancel request.

field.name: Symbol
field.description: For Mass Cancel scenario, providing a value here will result in all orders for that symbol be canceled. For canceling orders in different symbols the value should be '*'.

field.name: LowerThanPrice
field.description: For Mass Cancel scenario, Any order with a lower or equal limit price would be included in the cancel filter. This filter can only be used win conjunction with specific symbol.

field.name: HigherThanPrice
field.description: For Mass Cancel scenario, Any order with a higher or equal limit price would be included in the cancel filter. This filter can only be used win conjunction with specific symbol.

sbe:message.name: ExecutionReport_Trade
sbe:message.description: An unsolicited response triggered as a result of a trade. The message contains all the data describing trade.

field.description: OrderID is required to be unique for each chain of orders.

field.description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by the exchange Uniqueness is guaranteed within a single trading day.

field.description: Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill. Required if ExecType(150) = Trade or Trade Correct.

field.description: Price of this (last) fill. Required if ExecType(150) = Trade or Trade Correct

field.name: LeavesQty

field.description: Total quantity (e.g. number of shares) filled.

field.name: LastLiquidityInd
field.description: Indicator to identify whether this fill was a result of a liquidity provider providing or liquidity taker taking the liquidity.

field.name: LastMkt
field.description: Market of execution for last fill, or an indication of the market where an order was routed.
